Name: adult central nervous system teratoma
Definition: A leukemia that arises from changes in the tissues forming white blood cells and characterized by a normal or decreased number of white blood cells in the circulating blood.
Synonym: teratoma of the adult central nervous system

Name: central nervous system mature teratoma
Definition: A mature teratoma that is located_in the central nervous system.

Name: central nervous system immature teratoma
Definition: A malignant teratoma that is located_in the central nervous system.
